President Obama called Arkansas Governor Mike Beebe to receive an update on the severe weather in the state. The President expressed his condolences for the families who lost a loved one and his concern for those who are still missing. He also thanked the first responders for their heroic efforts and directed Administrator Craig Fugate to travel to Arkansas and ensure that federal resources are being used to support the state and local efforts. The President asked the Governor to inform him of any additional resources that could be provided to help the impacted communities.